    <h3 class="subtitle">Tools:</h3>
    <p>Glue, Pencil, Scissors, Ruler, Glue Gun</p>

    <h3 class="subtitle">Materials:</h3>
    <p>Cardboard, Bond/Wrapping paper</p>

    <h3 class="subtitle">Steps:</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>1. Cut the cardboard into 4 pieces with the size 25 cm x 9 cm</li><li>2. Glue all the 4 cardboards on top of each other</li><li>3. Cut another new cardboard into 6 pieces with the size 25 cm x 2 cm</li><li>4. Glue the cardboard to the edge of the 4 stacked cardboards</li><li>5. Cut another new cardboard into 4 pieces where the outer left side is 12.5 cm, the outer upper side is 23.5 cm, and the outer right side is 12.5 cm</li><li>6. Cut the inner left and right side to be 10 cm and the inner upper side to be 18.5 cm</li><li>7. Take off any excess cardboard and cut the edge of the left and right side stand into 2.5 cm each</li><li>8. Glue all the 4 cardboards on top of each other</li><li>9. Cut another new cardboard into 6 pieces with the size 25 cm x 2 cm</li><li>10. Cover all the edges of the 'c' shaped cardboard that was already stacked</li><li>11. Cut another new cardboard into 3 pieces with the size 8.5 cm x 5.5 cm</li><li>12. Glue the 3 pieces on top of each other</li><li>13. Repeat steps 11-12 three times to make 3 different cards</li><li>14. Once done, make a small hole in the upper middle for it to hang</li><li>15. Take a piece of paper and cut out numbers and months</li><li>16. Glue the 'c' shaped stand on top of the 4 stacked cardboards to make a stand</li><li>17. Cut another cardboard into 3 pieces with the size 12 cm x 1 cm</li><li>18. Hang the 3 pieces of string into the hole that has been created</li><li>19. Loop the end of each card onto the hanger</li><li>20. Flip the cards to change dates and months</li>
    </ol>

